file.name: azure.com-cdn-2016-04-02-swagger.yaml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  description: Use these APIs to manage Azure CDN resources through the Azure Resource
    Manager. You must make sure that requests made to these resources are
    secure. For more information, see
    https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/azure/dn790557.aspx.
  title: CdnManagementClient
  version: 2016-04-02
  x-apisguru-categories:
    - cloud
  x-logo:
    url: https://assets.onestore.ms/cdnfiles/onestorerolling-1606-01000/shell/v3/images/logo/microsoft.png
  x-origin:

      url: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Azure/azure-rest-api-specs/master/specification/cdn/resource-manager/Microsoft.Cdn/stable/2016-04-02/cdn.json
      version: "2.0"

  x-providerName: azure.com
  x-serviceName: cdn
  x-tags:
    - Azure
    - Microsoft
security:

paths:
  /providers/Microsoft.Cdn/checkNameAvailability:
    post:
      operationId: NameAvailability_CheckNameAvailability
      parameters:
        - $ref: "#/components/parameters/apiVersionParameter"
      requestBody:
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/CheckNameAvailabilityInput"
        description: Input to check.
        required: true
      responses:
        "200":
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/CheckNameAvailabilityOutput"
        default:
          description: CDN error response describing why the operation failed.
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/ErrorResponse"
      summary: Check the availability of a resource name without creating the resource.
        This is needed for resources where name is globally unique, such as a
        CDN endpoint.
      tags:
        - CheckNameAvailability
